Reasoning: The paper describes a new Big Data Management System (BDMS) with a flexible NoSQL style data model, a query language that supports a wide range of queries, and scalable runtime. These features make it well-suited to applications like web data warehousing, social data storage and analysis, and other use cases related to Big Data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
